description:
  Given a homogeneous k-th order differential operator A (D) on \R^n between
two finite dimensional spaces, we establish the Hardy inequality \[\int_{\R^n}
\frac{\abs{D^{k-1}u}}{\abs{x}} \dif x \leq C \int_{\R^n} \abs{A(D)u}\] and the
Sobolev inequality \[\norm{D^{k-n} u}_{L^{\infty}(\R^n)}\leq C \int_{\R^n}
\abs{A(D)u}\] when A(D) is elliptic and satisfies a recently introduced
cancellation property. We also study the necessity of these two conditions.

Comment: 16 pages, 5 figures, 1 appendix; expanded and refined discussion of
  gluing conditions and their connection to different ways of gapping the edge;
  published version

  {\small In this paper, we find a class of division quaternion algebras over
the field }$\mathbb{Q}\left( i\right) ${\small \ and a class of division symbol
algebras over a cyclotomic field.}
